<template description="Read Topology (from Stream)" category="tutorial"><line># After a Topolgy has been written by T.writeTopo() it </line><line># can be read back with T.readTopo().</line><line># readTopo expects a stream and so the StringIO class</line><line># is used here to read the topology from a String.</line><line></line><line>topo_data = &quot;&quot;&quot;</line><line>00    0.00    0.00</line><line>01   10.00    0.00</line><line>02   20.00    0.00</line><line>03    0.00   10.00</line><line>04   10.00   10.00</line><line>05   20.00   10.00</line><line>06    0.00   20.00</line><line>07   10.00   20.00</line><line>08   20.00   20.00</line><line>&quot;&quot;&quot;</line><line></line><line>import StringIO</line><line>topo_stream = StringIO.StringIO(topo_data)</line><line></line><line>_=T.readTopo(topo_stream)</line></template>